e interactions of real people in real situations.This timely collection is not intended as an even-handed review of the debate, but as a deliberately polemical intervention which aims to highlight some of the ways in which its central terms have been misconceived.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgent (Philosophy). 0aSocial structure. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aAnthony Giddens.  aJurgen Habermas.  aKarl Marx.  aMichel Foucault.  aPierre Bourdieu.  acontemporary social theory.  ahuman agents.  asocial structure.  asociological thought.  astructuration theory.  astructure-agency dualisms.1 aButton, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavanagh, Allison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDenis, Alex, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDennis, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Peter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Peter J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSharrock, Wes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909519140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719095191423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719095191/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles